sentences: Ida Vivado Orsini (1913–1989) was a Chilean pianist and composer.
She graduated from the National Conservatory of Music in Chile with a degree in Interpretation in 1941 and took a position on the faculty at the National Conservatory.
She received a scholarship to study in Italy in 1958 and studied instrumentation with Salvador Candianni.
Vivado married Don Marco Bontá, who died in 1974.
She published the article "Alberto Spikin" in Reviste Musical Chilena (April–June 1972).
Ocho Trozos, piano for four hands (1974)
Tres Poemsa y una Canzion for voice and piano (1949)
Tres Preludios y Tema con Variaciones for piano (1952)
Series Alternadas for piano (1986)Her music has been recorded and issued on CD:
National Association of Composers of Chile (ANC), SVR, Audio CD (1998).
After completing her studies, Vivado worked as a composer, and served as president of the National Association of Composers of Chile (ANC) from 1971-73.
